text: Lisbet Arredondo Reyes (born 22 November 1987) is a Cuban female volleyball player. She played for the Cuba women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2009 Women's NORCECA Volleyball Championship, 2009 Pan-American Games, 2007 Montreux Volley Masters, 2009 Montreux Volley Masters, 2010 Montreux Volley Masters, and 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for Villa Clara, Volejbol Kluby Šygys, Yeşilyurt, Gresik Petrokimia Volleyball Club, Hämeenlinnan Pallokerho Naiset, CV Logroño, and IBSA Palmas. == References == == Other websites == * Former Cuban National Team member Lisbet Arredondo Reyes to reinforce Generika Ayala Lifesavers Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Cuban volleyball players
